gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nuggets 117, Pacers 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Nuggets defeated the Pacers, 117-109. The Nuggets had four scorers with 20 or more points with Nikola Jokic totaling 25 points, 12 rebounds, and nine assists, and Jamal Murray (25 points, eight assists), Michael Porter Jr. (25 points, seven 3PT, eight rebounds, five assists), and Aaron Gordon (20 points, 10 rebounds) adding 70 points. Bruce Brown led Indiana with 18 points, 10 rebounds, and six assists as Buddy Hield added 16 points. The Nuggets improve to 28-13 on the year as the loss snaps a three-game win streak for Indiana, and they move to 23-16.
